The paper deals with the management of negation in logic programming, which is a topic closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents an alternative characterization of stable model semantics based on algebraic operators, which is a topic related to logic and set theory (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the closed world assumption, which is a topic related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper's approach is purely algebraic, which is a topic related to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on stable model semantics is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
